Sun Jul  5 09:49:18 UTC 2026 - Dirk Müller <dmueller@suse.com>

- update to 0.4.5 (bsc#1270285, CVE-2026-49825):
  * Fixed a security vulnerability where javascript: URLs in
    xlink:href attributes were not sanitized
    when``safe_attrs_only=False``, allowing cross-site scripting
    (XSS) attacks. The fix requires lxml>=6.1.1, which adds
    xlink:href to the set of link attributes iterated by
    rewrite_links(). Reported by Guillem Lefait (@glefait).

-------------------------------------------------------------------
Tue Mar 10 09:58:53 UTC 2026 - Nico Krapp <nico.krapp@suse.com>

- Update to 0.4.4
  * Fixed a bug where Unicode escapes in CSS were not properly decoded before
    security checks. This prevents attackers from bypassing filters using
    escape sequences. (CVE-2026-28348) (bsc#1259378)
  * Fixed a security issue where <base> tags could be used for URL hijacking
    attacks. The <base> tag is now automatically removed whenever the <head>
    tag is removed (via page_structure=True or manual configuration), as <base>
    must be inside <head> according to HTML specifications. (CVE-2026-28350)
    (bsc#1259379)

-------------------------------------------------------------------
Fri Oct 10 05:38:18 UTC 2025 - Steve Kowalik <steven.kowalik@suse.com>

- Update to 0.4.3:
